video.title: Sword Art Online
video.synopsis: A video game whiz helps create a new technology that enables players to guide their online avatars with their own bodies -- but a dark twist emerges.

episodes.synopsis: It's officially launch day as Sword Art Online -- one of the most eagerly awaited video games of all time -- is released.
episodes.title: The World of Swords

episodes.synopsis: Though the players have been locked in the game for a month, the first floor hasn't been cleared yet -- and 2,000 people have died.
episodes.title: Beater

episodes.synopsis: When Kirito joins a guild composed of close friends in reality, everything goes well -- until a tragic accident changes him completely.
episodes.title: The Red-Nosed Reindeer

episodes.synopsis: After quarreling with her party's leader, young beast-tamer Silica storms off but loses her way in the forest -- where she runs into monsters.
episodes.title: The Black Swordsman

episodes.synopsis: When a player is killed inside a safe zone, Asuna and Kirito take it upon themselves to find out how and why it happened.
episodes.title: Murder in the Safe Zone

episodes.synopsis: Kirito and Asuna investigate a murder that should have been impossible within the game -- only to see a new victim perish before their eyes.
episodes.title: Illusionary Avenger

episodes.synopsis: A customer arrives at Lisbeth's blacksmith shop, requesting that she make him the best sword possible.
episodes.title: The Temperature of the Heart

episodes.synopsis: After two years, players are used to living in the game. But with a dwindling frontline, it may be up to Kirito and Asuna to continue the charge.
episodes.title: The Sword Dance of Black and White

episodes.synopsis: Teaming with Asuna, Kirito clears the dungeon on the 74th floor. They discover the Boss Room but flee once they spot the boss.
episodes.title: The Blue-Eyed Demon

episodes.synopsis: With Asuna's freedom hanging in the balance, Kirito agrees to duel the leader of the Knights of the Blood Oath.
episodes.title: Crimson Killing Intent

episodes.synopsis: Newlyweds Kirito and Asuna are enjoying their time away from the frontlines -- but a new arrival soon takes them all the way back to the beginning.
episodes.title: The Girl of Morning Dew

episodes.synopsis: Yulier, the Liberation Army's second in command, asks Kirito and Asuna for help to save a friend -- and her guild.
episodes.title: Yui's Heart

episodes.synopsis: While enjoying a fishing tournament, Kirito receives an urgent message from the guild leader, requesting his return.
episodes.title: Edge of Hell's Abyss

episodes.synopsis: The battle against the Skull Reaper -- boss of the 75th floor -- turns out to be more ferocious than anyone imagined, yielding a host of casualties.
episodes.title: The End of the World

episodes.synopsis: Kirigaya is adjusting to life outside the game but hasn't forgotten about Asuna, who has yet to awaken.
episodes.title: Return

episodes.synopsis: Going in search of Asuna, Kirito joins a new MMO that allows users to fly -- and encourages player killing.
episodes.title: Land of the Fairies

episodes.synopsis: As Leafa schools Kirito about the game and the hatred between the races, Asuna learns the truth about her role from the fairy king.
episodes.title: Captive Queen

episodes.synopsis: Leafa makes enemies by leaving her group to team up with Kirito.
episodes.title: To the World Tree

episodes.synopsis: When Recon sends Leafa a cryptic message, will she and Kirito have time to figure it out before they come under attack?
episodes.title: The Legrue Corridor

episodes.synopsis: Kirito's plan to prevent a war between the races may work -- if he can survive a fight against a Salamander general.
episodes.title: General of the Blazing Flame

episodes.synopsis: Kirito and the others finally reach the largest city in Alfheim, located at the foot of the World Tree.
episodes.title: The Truth About Alfheim

episodes.synopsis: Kirito's determination to save Asuna borders on insanity. But his recklessness comes to a halt when Leafa suddenly logs out.
episodes.title: The Grand Quest

episodes.synopsis: Even though a wall has been built between Suguha and Kirito, he must save Asuna.
episodes.title: Bonds

episodes.synopsis: Kirito, Asuna and Yui are reunited, but the chains put on Asuna are unbreakable. Before they can devise a plan, the fairy king makes his entrance.
episodes.title: Gilded Hero

episodes.synopsis: Kazuto Kirigaya has beaten death twice, but there's one more thing he must do before he can see Asuna in the real world.
episodes.title: The World Seed

episodes.synopsis: When a new game called Gun Gale Online proves lethal in real life, the government asks Kazuto to join the game and investigate the incidents.
episodes.title: The World of Guns

episodes.synopsis: Inside the Gun Gale Online gaming world, a squadron led by an elite sniper named Sinon takes on an unexpectedly robust foe.
episodes.title: Cold-Hearted Sniper

episodes.synopsis: Sinon's controller, Shino, recalls a traumatic gun-related incident from her past. Meanwhile, Kirito tells Asuna of his plans to join Gun Gale Online.
episodes.title: Memories of Fresh Blood

episodes.synopsis: Now inside Gun Gale Online, Kirito plans to smoke out Death Gun by joining Bullet of Bullets, a tournament to determine the game's best gunman.
episodes.title: GGO

episodes.synopsis: Realizing that they may have to fight each other in the Bullet of Bullets, Sinon and Kirito vow to go all-out if they end up in a faceoff.
episodes.title: Guns and Swords

episodes.synopsis: Kirito recalls the trauma of the Sword Art Online incident. He fights Sinon but stubbornly refuses to beat her despite his superior skills.
episodes.title: Showdown in the Wilderness

episodes.synopsis: Suguha confronts Kazuto about his activities in the online world as he grapples with having killed people in the Sword Art Online incident.
episodes.title: Crimson Memories

episodes.synopsis: Believing that Death Gun will reveal himself during the Bullet of Bullets, Kirito and Sinon set an ambush while the melee rages around them.
episodes.title: Bullet of Bullets

episodes.synopsis: Death Gun reveals himself, and Kirito and Sinon decide to join forces to take him down before there are any more casualties.
episodes.title: Death Gun

episodes.synopsis: After Kirito saves Sinon from Death Gun's bullet at the last moment, the two flee on mechanical horses and take refuge in a cave to regroup.
episodes.title: Death Chaser

episodes.synopsis: Having escaped Death Gun's trap, Kirito and Sinon theorize how he can kill people in real life while slaying their avatars within Gun Gale Online.
episodes.title: What It Means to Be Strong

episodes.synopsis: As the Bullet of Bullets tournament reaches its climax, Kirito and Sinon target Death Gun, but another contestant throws a wrench into the works.
episodes.title: Bullet of a Phantom

episodes.synopsis: Death Gun overpowers Kirito, putting him in danger. Sinon looks on and desperately tries to find a way to save him.
episodes.title: Phantom Bullet

episodes.synopsis: Kyuoji attacks Sinon, hoping to kill her and then kill himself, but Kazuto manages to save her, putting himself in great danger in the process.
episodes.title: One Small Step

episodes.synopsis: When the legendary sword Excalibur is rumored to be in an icy dungeon in Alfheim Online, Kirito, Sinon and their friends set out to find it first.
episodes.title: Queen of the Lake

episodes.synopsis: Kirito and company take on a giant in their quest to uncover Excalibur -- and learn that failing their task will trigger an in-game apocalypse.
episodes.title: King of the Giants

episodes.synopsis: The fight against the powerful ice giant guarding Excalibur proves to be more than the friends can handle. Freyja tells Kirito how to defeat him.
episodes.title: Excalibur

episodes.synopsis: Floors 21-30 are unlocked, and Asuna, Kirito and Yui hope to live together on Floor 22 ... if they can get past the boss on Floor 21.
episodes.title: House in the Forest

episodes.synopsis: After sparring with her mother over her future in the real world, Asuna takes on a brilliant challenger.
episodes.title: Zekken

episodes.synopsis: Asuna agrees to help the Sleeping Knights guild defeat a powerful floor boss, but a rival guild jeopardizes the success of their mission.
episodes.title: Sleeping Knights

episodes.synopsis: While Kirito battles the rival guild, the Sleeping Knights take on the floor boss. Asuna makes a request and is met with surprising resistance.
episodes.title: The Monument of the Swordsmen

episodes.synopsis: Back in the real world, Kazuto helps Asuna locate Yuuki, who reveals her tragic story and asks Asuna to meet with her again in Alfheim Online.
episodes.title: The End of the Journey

episodes.synopsis: After helping Yuuki realize her dream of attending school, Asuna begins to repair her fractured relationship with her mother.
episodes.title: The Dream Begins

episodes.synopsis: Yuuki's real-world condition worsens, and Asuna discovers a surprising connection to the Sword Art Online incident.
episodes.title: Mother's Rosario

episodes.synopsis: Shino takes a look back at the story so far, including the Bullet of Bullets tournament and the foiling of Death Gun, both inside the game and out.
episodes.title: Debriefing

episodes.synopsis: After their usual routine chopping away at the Gigas Cedar, Kirito and Eugeo join their friend Alice on a destiny-changing trip into a nearby cave.
episodes.title: Underworld

episodes.synopsis: Kirito wakes to unfamiliar surroundings but although he suspects that he's in a game, he can't log out. He soon encounters a boy his age named Eugeo.
episodes.title: The Demon Tree

episodes.synopsis: Kirito needs to finish off the Demon Tree once and for all so that he and Eugeo can head to the big city together. A sword he found may do the trick.
episodes.title: The End Mountains

episodes.synopsis: Kirito battles the goblins but their leader is too much for him to handle. Eugeo must conquer his fear and help him before it's too late.
episodes.title: Departure

episodes.synopsis: Kirito's situation isn't looking good and Kikuoka transfers him to another hospital. But when Asuna and Suguha go for a visit, they are denied entry.
episodes.title: Ocean Turtle

episodes.synopsis: Asuna and Rinko press Kikuoka for answers. He reveals the true aim of the Underworld experiment and the reasons for Kirito's involvement.
episodes.title: Project Alicization

episodes.synopsis: Two years have passed and Kirito and Eugeo are now trainees at a swordsmanship academy, where they must deal with some difficult senior students.
episodes.title: Swordcraft Academy

episodes.synopsis: Sortiliena warns Kirito that Uolo's request for a live duel is linked to an ulterior motive. Later, Kirito discovers his flowers have been destroyed.
episodes.title: Swordsman's Pride

episodes.synopsis: Even after his promotion, Eugeo is still searching for ways to become stronger. An opportunity presents itself in the form of top student Humbert.
episodes.title: Nobleman's Responsibilities

episodes.synopsis: While Kirito goes to look for the missing Ronye and Tiese, Eugeo hears something troubling from Frenica and decides to take matters into his own hands.
episodes.title: Taboo Index

episodes.synopsis: Eugeo recognizes the knight that takes him into custody but she doesn't appear to know him. Meanwhile in the real world, a strange robot appears.
episodes.title: Central Cathedral

episodes.synopsis: Eugeo and Kirito face the Integrity Knight Eldrie, who seems to resemble someone. Eugeo uses his knowledge of the real world to gain an advantage.
episodes.title: The Sage of the Library

episodes.synopsis: Kirito's savior reveals the history between her and the Administrator and how he and Eugeo can get Alice's memory back by assisting in her plan.
episodes.title: Ruler and Mediator

episodes.synopsis: Kirito and Eugeo find their stolen swords in the weapons warehouse. But it is no time to celebrate, Integrity Knight, Deusolbert, swoops down on them.
episodes.title: The Crimson Knight

episodes.synopsis: Eugeo and Kirito continue through the Central Cathedral and encounter two little girls who appear to be harmless. But there's more than meets the eye.
episodes.title: The Relentless Knight

episodes.synopsis: After the battle is over, Kirito is immediately more concerned about Fanatio than himself, and does everything he possibly can to save her.
episodes.title: The Osmanthus Knight

episodes.synopsis: Kirito and Alice find themselves in a precarious situation. He tries to get her to consider cooperating for now, but she still sees him as a criminal.
episodes.title: Truce

episodes.synopsis: Bercouli Synthesis One declares he will not kill Eugeo the first time they cross swords, but the promise is not repeated when Eugeo attacks again.
episodes.title: The Legendary Hero

episodes.synopsis: Alice decides to hear Kirito out but choosing to believe the truth of his words is no simple matter. Meanwhile, Eugeo wakes up on the 100th floor.
episodes.title: The Seal of the Right Eye

episodes.synopsis: Now awake, Alice mentions a detour to a bath on the 90th floor. She and Kirito are soon reunited with Bercouli, but he's been turned to stone.
episodes.title: Synthesis

episodes.synopsis: Alice watches as her childhood friends square off against each other. Kirito tries his best to get to the real Eugeo but the fight ends unexpectedly.
episodes.title: The 32nd Knight

episodes.synopsis: The battle against the Genie is not going well and Kirito decides to change tactics. The Administrator learns something important about him.
episodes.title: Titan of the Sword

episodes.synopsis: After hundreds of years, the Cardinal returns to settle things once and for all. The Administrator reveals a shocking truth about the Golem.
episodes.title: Administrator

episodes.synopsis: Eugeo and Alice are out of commission and Kirito must face the ultra-powerful Administrator on his own. She's got a few surprises in store for him.
episodes.title: My Hero
